.TH RDAP 1 "January 2025" "rdap 1.3.4" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
rdap \- simple RDAP client for querying domain, IP, and ASN registration data
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B rdap
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fIquery\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B rdap
is a lightweight RDAP (Registration Data Access Protocol) client that queries
registration data for domains, IP addresses, and autonomous system numbers (ASNs).
It requires only curl and optionally jq for formatted output.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-type " " \fItype\fR
Specify query type. Required for advanced queries. Types: ns, help, entity,
domain-search, domain-search-by-ns, domain-search-by-ns-ip, ns-search,
ns-search-by-ip, entity-search, entity-search-by-handle.
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-full
Full detailed output including all entities, events, and notices.
.TP
.BR \-R ", " \-\-registrar
Follow registrar RDAP link to get complete contact data (registrant, tech, admin).
.TP
.BR \-r ", " \-\-raw
Output raw JSON response.
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-server " " \fIurl\fR
Use specific RDAP server URL. Required for advanced query types.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Verbose output showing debug information.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display help message and exit.
.TP
.BR \-\-clear\-cache
Clear the IANA bootstrap cache.
.SH QUERY TYPES
Query types are auto-detected for basic queries:
.TP
.B domain
Any string containing a dot (e.g., example.com)
.TP
.B IPv4
Dotted decimal notation (e.g., 8.8.8.8)
.TP
.B IPv6
Colon-separated notation (e.g., 2001:4860:4860::8888)
.TP
.B ASN
AS followed by number, or number > 255 (e.g., AS13335 or 13335)
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Basic domain lookup:
.B rdap example.com
.TP
Full output:
.B rdap -f example.com
.TP
Follow registrar for complete data:
.B rdap -R example.com
.TP
IP address lookup:
.B rdap 8.8.8.8
.TP
ASN lookup:
.B rdap AS13335
.TP
Nameserver lookup:
.B rdap -t ns -s https://rdap.verisign.com/com/v1 ns1.google.com
.TP
Domain search:
.B rdap -t domain-search -s https://rdap.verisign.com/com/v1 'exam*.com'
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.cache/rdap/
Cache directory for IANA bootstrap data (24 hour TTL).
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B XDG_CACHE_HOME
If set, cache is stored in $XDG_CACHE_HOME/rdap instead of ~/.cache/rdap.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
Error (connection failure, not found, invalid query, etc.)
